li.p:
Just compute the linear combination using the coordinate vector components as coefficients, in the proper order:


		\uvec{w}
		\amp= 1\begin{bmatrix} 1 \amp 0 \\ 0 \amp 0 \end{bmatrix}
		+ 3\begin{bmatrix} 1 \amp 1 \\ 0 \amp 0 \end{bmatrix}
		+ 0\begin{bmatrix} 0 \amp 0 \\ 1 \amp 0 \end{bmatrix}
		+ (-2)\begin{bmatrix} 0 \amp 0 \\ 1 \amp 1 \end{bmatrix}

		\amp= \begin{bmatrix} 4 \amp 3 \\ -2 \amp -2 \end{bmatrix}.
